inn1.comm: Watson gets Australia off the mark with a boundary! A fine start as he reaches across to whip a lovely cover drive through the gap along the ground
fullish and swinging away, and Watson punches back past the bowler
a tighter line now from Anderson and Watson defends with bat and pad close together
another good cover drive, although this one has clunked a bit and hasn't been timed properly, it's chased down and they pick up two
good ball, just straightening a touch without being prodigious outswing, and Watson defends
defended again to the off side
swinging on to the pads now and Haddin gets a leg bye
again it's the wrong line as Shahzad swings it well down leg, Watson clips it away for a single
better line now, outside off and Haddin leaves it alone
swinging down leg once again, Haddin cops it on the body as he can't get bat on ball
oh dear, well down leg again and this one goes through to Prior and is called a wide
inswing again but it's on the stumps now and Haddin softly whips a single through square leg
good ball, nipping in off a good length and Watson keeps it out
fullish and just outside off, Haddin drives but can't beat mid-off
good ball from Anderson, probing just outside off and swinging away a fraction, Haddin defends

that's a cracking, punchy off-drive from Haddin. Really terrific timing as he just leans in to that shot and pushes it back past the bowler, Pietersen at mid-off dives across and can't save it, though he perhaps should have
driven away to the off side again
angling in to the pads of Watson, who nudges a quick single through midwicket
down leg side again and Haddin gets a single
left alone outside off, and that's carried high and quick through to Prior
attacking the off stump now and Haddin defends
Shahzad goes for the bouncer now, and Haddin ducks underneath it - after some consultation Rod Tucker and Asad Rauf decide that was legal, though it probably was too high
good ball, nipping back quite sharply off the seam and sailing over off stump as it's left alone
Haddin gets right in behind this one to defend
ah, Shahzad had bowled a much better line this over but he ruins it by straying way down leg again
well outside off and Haddin guides it off the face of the bat down to third man
down leg side, another wide, from Anderson this time
and another one swings on to the pads, this one strikes Haddin on the body
good bouncer - well directed and Haddin had to sway quickly out of the way to avoid taking that on the helmet
good bounce and carry again as Haddin leaves one outside off
ouch! This one has jagged back in at 143kph and whacks Haddin in the midriff
Haddin responds with a drive but not timed quite well enough to get past Pietersen at mid-off

Watson hasn't had much of the strike the past couple of overs and he doesn't waste this delivery! Anderson dropped just a touch short and Watson lashed a pull forward of midwicket, super timing and that was always a boundary
Shahzad goes for the yorker now but slightly off line, and Haddin keeps it out
Haddin tries to work it through leg but there's a man at a sort of leg gully or short backward square leg, who cuts this off
well played, though it was a bad ball, short and down leg, and Haddin just helps this on its way over the leg gully and there's nobody at fine leg who can save this boundary
Shahzad's line is all over the place, now he goes a bit short and wide and Haddin cuts hard on the bounce to third man
angles on to the pads of Watson, who gently clips a single to midwicket
fuller and wide of off, Haddin tries to drive but can't time it
fullish length to start with and Watson drives it back to the bowler
good line right on off stump and Watson punches to cover
Finn goes really full again, Watson crunches it back over the bowler's head on the bounce but it's collected safely by mid-off
this one is driven harder along the ground past the bowler but it's only a single as Pietersen at mid-off does well to dive across and save this
good ball - Finn goes for the yorker with the angle in to Haddin and there's half an appeal for lbw but that was sliding down leg
strays down leg now and that one's a wide
another good yorker from Finn and Haddin jams the bat down to keep it out
soft hands from Watson as he gets a single with a push towards gully
Shahzad angles this in to Haddin, who defends
Haddin has got tired of waiting and backs off a touch to slash an upper cut over point, racing away to the boundary. The ball was short and wide enough to justify that shot, and he played it well

and another boundary, though this one was a more genuine edge. But he went hard, and it flew over the vacant second slip area - he'd have to have been Joel Garner to have any hope, even if there was a man there - and it bounces away to third man
defended away to the leg side
another bad ball swinging down leg from Shahzad, and Prior can't quite take it cleanly
solidly defended to off

there's an lbw shout as Finn angles it in to Watson, but Rod Tucker isn't interested. It looked to be sliding down leg but Strauss wants a review. Hmm, it's hit him in line but he's quite a way forward, and the replays confirm that is missing leg. So England have lost one of their two reviews.
Finn tries for the yorker again but it's just a touch half-volleyish and Watson drives a single wide of mid-off
this one's a very good yorker - Haddin can do nowt but keep it out
oh, what a cracking off-drive but he's hit it so hard that mid-off, who is back on the edge of the circle, collects it so quickly they can't get a single
ah, Finn gives Haddin just a little width outside off and Haddin backs off a touch to slash a cut over point, really well played
fuller and angled in, hits Haddin on the pad as he can't get it away
Watson pushes to off, can't find the gap
Woakes strikes! Watson goes for a hard cut behind point but he's picked out Collingwood, whose reflexes have not dulled at all! He takes a really good, sharp catch and Watson is on his way
Woakes comes around the wicket to Marsh, who defends
angling on to the pads of Marsh, who tries to whip through square leg but can't find a gap
fullish and angling in again, Marsh meets it with the full face of the bat
Marsh gets off the mark with a flick off his hips behind square leg as Woakes strays a touch
well now, this one has really fizzed through past the outside edge and thumps into Prior's gloves - good ball
straighter line now and Haddin defends
Finn uses his angle and bounce to nip it in to Haddin from short of a length and it flies away off the thigh just wide of gully for a leg bye
Marsh walks across and covers his off stump, and leaves it alone
swinging on to the pads and Marsh turns a single to fine leg
soft hands from Haddin, who nudges a single to the leg side
Haddin drops this one at his feet and thinks about a quick single, but Marsh sends him back
oh, Haddin is lucky to get away with this one as Woakes angles it back in and draws an inside edge that clips the back leg and sails just over the top of the stumps
this time Haddin gets a single as he pushes gently back past the bowler towards mid-on
England persist with the angle in to Marsh, trying to deny him runs to the off side, and he flicks it through midwicket
pushes this one away defensively towards point
again Marsh clips a run behind square leg - plenty of gaps on the leg side for him
banged in a little short and outside off, Marsh uses the bounce on this to steer a cut safely over gully and it runs away to third man
Finn squares Marsh up this time with a ball on off stump, it gets a thickish edge away through gully
Finn gives Haddin some extra bounce now and he tries to back away for his old favourite slash, but this one just clunks down into the ground and bounces through to Prior
swinging on to the pads of Haddin, who gets a leg bye
left alone outside off
fullish on off stump, Marsh clips a single towards mid-on
banged in at the hips of Marsh, who helps this on its way to fine leg
Woakes comes wide of the crease and angles it in to Haddin, who shapes to back away and then defends

cracker! Haddin gets tired of this and gives himself some room and then powers this back over the bowler's head, and that is timed so well as it races away to the boundary straight back down the ground
more room for Haddin, who steers this one to third man
Marsh leans forward with bat and pad close together and defends
good ball, the yorker coming in from around the wicket keeps Marsh back and all he can do is defend
once more Haddin backs away to the leg side and tries to force it through off, but this one doesn't find the gap

fullish ball and Haddin tries to muscle this drive over mid-off, Pietersen is back on the circle and it's just gone safely wide of him in the air - it still wasn't timed that well but Pietersen's chase can't cut it off - he was going to dive and then decided not to
pushed away to the off side

well, Brad Haddin's walking around in the crease has cost him now, and he's been bowled through his legs! Finn gets his first ODI wicket as Haddin tries to move across to the off side and clip through leg, but he's missed it completely and the ball goes through his legs to bowl him
bouncer to begin with, and Prior does very well to leap up and prevent this running away for five wides - it'll just be the one wide
Clarke takes a big stride across to shoulder arms outside off
another one left alone by Clarke
swings this one too far down leg and that's a wide
swinging in again to Marsh, who gets it off the pad and this ball runs to Prior, not missing the leg stump by a great margin
full and swinging in, Marsh drives back to the bowler
another fullish ball just outside off, Marsh tries to drive through cover but Bell collects it
good, hard running as Marsh picks up two with another clip through midwicket
banged in a touch shorter on the hips, Marsh just guides this one to fine leg for another single
Clarke gets off the mark with a solid punch through the gap at cover and he's quick enough between the wickets to turn that into three runs
another crisp shot, Clarke leans forward and across to flick a full ball with terrific timing between mid-on and midwicket
better line on off stump, Clarke strides forward and defends with a straight bat
Yes! yells Clarke after nudging a length delivery off his pads on the leg side
good length delivery outside off, Marsh lets it go through to Prior
Finn angles a full ball into the left-hander's off and middle stump from round the wicket, Marsh digs it out
wider outside off stump this time, Marsh strides forward and shoulders arms with a flourish
short of a length just outside off, Clarke moves towards the ball and punches to cover point, his timing is good today
played off the front foot towards cover again, the length was fuller around off from Anderson
a touch straight and Clarke works the ball wide of mid-on for a single
good length angling across Marsh from over the wicket, played from the crease towards point
pushed off the front foot towards mid off
Anderson pitches short of a length outside leg, Marsh waits and pulls it off his hips towards fine leg
full ball angling into Marsh from round the wicket. No room to work with and he defends with bat and pad close together
Marsh tries to work the ball on the leg but gets an inside edge on to the pad towards the off side, Clarke calls him through for a quick single
defended on the front foot towards the off side
Finn angles the ball at Clarke's body from over the wicket, Clarke fends towards the leg side, Finn has a forward short leg in place and Clarke got hit on the glove while fending
slapped, Clarke backs away to make room and goes hard at a short ball, flaying it through cover with power and timing
straight this time, Clarke punches down the ground off the front foot, between the stumps and the non-striker and his timing is outstanding

And he's struck right away! He angled a gentle delivery into Marsh at 117 kph, it pitched on a good length and Marsh came forward to flick. He hit it cleanly but in the air towards midwicket where Strauss dived forward and to hi left to take a low catch. An extremely soft dismissal.
Collingwood goes over the wicket to the right-handers and bowls a wider delivery outside off, White lets it go
fuller ball and straighter line, White clips towards midwicket
defended on the front foot towards the leg side
straight and simple bowling from  Collingwood. White gets behind the line and defends towards the off
no width or length to work with and White has to defend once again towards the off side
and he begins with one on Clarke's pads and watches the batsman flick towards fine leg
Woakes tests White with the short ball, White shapes up to pull but then bails out of the shot
was that edged or steered? A bit of both perhaps but he placed it fine past the wicketkeeper to the third-man boundary
White goes hard at a wide ball outside off but mis-times the cut towards point
good length, angling into the right-hander, White pushes towards the leg side and runs
Clarke strides forward to defend a good length ball around off stump with confidence
up and over! White gets under a length delivery and hoists it straight back over Collingwood's head for six. The field was in but he cleared the boundary by a few yards
driven fluently off the front foot wide of the fielder at mid-off for a boundary
defended on the off side on the front foot
defended confidently once again on the front foot
Collingwood bowls a tight line on off and middle but Whites pushes the ball past him and calls for the quick single
Clarke moves forward and flicks the ball off middle stump towards midwicket
defended on the front foot towards cover

he's gone! And that is some delivery. Woakes pitched on a good length after angling the ball into the right-hander and got it to straighten off the pitch. White was squared up in his crease and his attempt at defending resulted in a sizeable edge to Matt Prior
good length angling into Hussey. He defends on the off side
too full and too straight, flicked off the pads through midwicket
short ball and Clarke ducks under it
pushed off the front foot towards point
driven off the front foot towards cover
Collingwood bowls a tight line on off stump, pushed towards cover
Clarke moves forward and across, pushes the ball firmly to mid-on and continues running
good length and extremely straight. Hussey plays the ball back towards Collingwood
120 kph, Hussey drives towards cover on the front foot
Hussey drives the ball firmly but back to the bowler
full ball on middle stump, Clarke moves forward and across and plays to mid-on
good length and straight, defended on the front foot towards the off side
short and wide and Clarke cuts the ball hard in front of point, Trott fields on the boundary and the batsman run the third on the throw
Hussey strides forward and drives fluently through extra cover for two more
full and straight, driven back to the bowler on the front foot
played back to the bowler once again to end the over
driven off the front foot through cover for a single
Collignwood pitches on middle and Hussey uses the angle and flicks through square
Clarke closes the face of the bat and plays towards midwicket
Clarke moves across and defends from his crease with bat and pad close together
full ball on off and middle, Clarke moves forward and drives towards mid on
full ball wide outside off, 103 kph, Clarke mis-times the cover drive but hits it wide of the man at short cover
good length delivery outside off, Clarke lets it go
defended back to the bowler.
pushed off the front foot towards mid-on
full ball angling into middle and leg, Hussey flicks the ball through midwicket for two more
Hussey tries to defend but gets an inside edge on to the pad
Clarke strides forward and defends on the off side. Collingwood is bowling so simply, wicket to wicket at 120 kph or so and the batsman can't do much
defended once again towards the bowler
Clarke comes forward to drive and makes good contact, Collingwood reaches out with his right hand and fields on his follow through
tight stuff continues, Clarke defends with bat and pad close together
flicked off the pads through midwicket for a single
Hussey drives off the front foot towards Collingwood's left and the bowlers fields. Just one run off that over.
good length delivery angling into the right-hander, Clarke defends
Clarke defends from his crease towards the bowler
Clarke tries to run the single to mid-on but there's no run there
driven off the front foot towards cover. Clarke has stagnated after a fluent start to his innings
Clarke strides forward and defends a good length ball towards the off. The Gabba crowd is stirring up some noise
defended from the crease towards cover. A maiden to follow a one-run over. Pressure mounting.
full ball outside off, Hussey uses the width to drive through cover point
Clarke pushes the ball off the front foot towards mid-on and sets off as soon as he makes contact
Hussey works the ball from its middle-stump line towards cover
full and straight, driven past the bowler and mid-on runs and slides to his left to keep the batsmen to one
Clarke uses the width outside off to dab the ball towards third man
Hussey this time, opens the face late to dab the ball from off stump towards third man where Shahzad does the fielding
left alone outside off stump
short, wide, smashed. Hussey reaches out for a wide one and lashes the ball through point with a fierce cut
this wasn't that short, it wasn't that wide and it bounced a touch more to beat Hussey's cut
Hussey attempts to drive straight but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards third man
Clarke moves forward, pushes towards cover and calls immediately
Hussey gets another outside edge towards third man for a single
full ball on off stump, Hussey times the drive well but places it to the fielder at cover
full ball on middle, worked off the pads through the leg side
Clarke tales two steps forward and plays the ball towards midwicket
flicked off the pads through midwicket for a single
Hussey defends from his crease towards point
Hussey moves forward to flick and plays it straight to midwicket
the first ball is a touch wide outside off and Clarke steers the ball towards third man, 116.8 kph
driven and driven superbly wide of the fielder at mid-off, excellent timing
played on the leg side off the front foot
pushed from the crease down the ground for a single, 115kph that was
played down the ground towards long on again
the slower ball at 104.9kph, Hussey waits for it and pushes the ball through cover for  a single
driven off the front foot through cover again
good length and very straight. Clarke moves forward and across to play the ball towards mid-on
pushed off the front foot towards midwicket
a touch too full and straight, Clarke flicks through midwicket
played from the crease towards midwicket
full on middle again, Clarke leans across and flicks the ball through midwicket
cracking drive through extra cover from Clarke as the changed ball offers a bit of pace off the bat, and Steven Finn, who has returned, goes a touch too full
defended back down the pitch
angling on to the pads now and it's whipped through square leg
and Hussey goes for a good cover drive now as he gets some width outside off, but Pietersen at deep cover keeps this to two
driven back past the bowler towards mid-off
angles this one in to the off stump and Hussey guides it to gully
beaten outside off as Clarke tries to force Collingwood through point, Prior whips the bails off but Clarke didn't lift his foot
swings on to the pads now and Clarke glances a single to fine leg
Hussey drives straight back to Collingwood
another pretty straight ball and Hussey tickles it fine enough to pick up a couple of runs
driven down towards long-on and it's another single
another one right on off stump and Clarke works it to mid-on
short of a length from Finn and Hussey nudges to point
Hussey ducks a bouncer now
angling on to the hips of Hussey, who turns a single past square leg
another one is on the hips, another one is flicked through square leg to the man in the deep
ah, Finn gets this bouncer wrong as it sails down leg side and is called a wide
good, quick single as Hussey gets on the back foot and nudges to cover
Clarke uses his feet now and gives himself room to pull a slightly short ball through midwicket, well placed by Clarke as he finds the gap at midwicket and picks up a valuable boundary
Hussey pushes another single through cover, keeps the score ticking along
Clarke flicks a single through midwicket now
a touch short and wide outside off and Hussey cuts hard in the air, it bounces down to third man
tickled away behind square leg and they can't turn this into two runs as KP fields
good, consistent line on off stump and Hussey punches through cover
Collingwood finishes with a slower ball, yorker length outside off and Clarke can't get a run back past the bowler

and Woakes' fine day continues! Hussey has dragged it on, trying to cut hard outside off and the ball cannons in to the off stump. The ball was there to be hit, he just didn't get it off the middle, and perhaps a touch of seam in to the batsman also contributed
Smith is off the mark straight away, with a defensive push to cover that he turns into a quick single
pushed away to the off side
left alone outside off, good line from Woakes
fullish and angling in, Clarke gets forward and nudges to off
Clarke drives through cover now and gets a single that takes him to 49 and allows him to retain the strike
short and wide of off to start with and that brings Clarke his half-century, as he cuts a single forward of point
Smith pushes a single wide of cover, in much the same way as he got off the mark
Clarke cuts but can only get a single to deep point
bad ball, way down leg side and that's a bonus run for the Aussies
on the pads and Smith tries to clip through midwicket, can't find the gap
angling in to off stump, Smith just pushes to mid-off
Smith opens the face now and runs a single down to third man
another one is driven wide of cover by Smith, who is happy to get a few singles to start with and get his eye in
Clarke goes over the top now, he's pulled deliberately high over midwicket and it just chips safely wide of the man in the deep, a couple of runs for the captain
drives one through cover now
Woakes swings this one down leg and Smith clips it uppishly down to fine leg

oh, that's a disappointing end for Clarke after he built such a good platform. He has walked at Woakes and tried to pull over midwicket, but this skies off a top edge and doesn't travel very far, Strauss runs in from cover to take a very simple catch and Woakes has his fourth
cut away to point and Smith can't beat Collingwood
Johnson leaves his first ball outside off
a touch slower at 131kph and Johnson drives, checking his shot just enough to avoid pushing a caught and bowled back
even slower now at 126kph, and Johnson defends this one
beaten outside off! Anderson gets some really good angle across just outside off and Johnson doesn't get the bat anywhere near it
defended - could this be a maiden?
driven to mid-off, and indeed that was a very valuable maiden over from Anderson
Smith defends to the off side
slower delivery now and Smith nudges a single wide of cover
Johnson still can't get off the mark, he nudges it to leg, to the only man on that side of the pitch in the circle
he is off the mark now with an edge that runs away to third man for two runs
clipped off the pads now for a run to fine leg
Smith pushes defensively to the off side and can't find a gap
Johnson drives and can't beat the man at short cover
another dot ball as Johnson simply can't find the gaps, this time hitting to point
and he gets a single now, just jamming out a fullish ball to the leg side
a bit of inswing and Smith drives to cover
Smith swivels this one around through midwicket for another single
there's a bonus for Australia as Anderson sprays it down leg
Anderson attacks off stump and all Johnson manages is a defensive nudge down the pitch
Smith drives through cover but can only get a single
goes for the yorker and Johnson drives a single towards mid-off
a good slower ball from Shahzad and Smith wound up for a big slog over cover, but the change of pace was too good for the batsman to connect, although they do snaffle a bye
bouncer, Johnson goes for the pull and gets a top edge that sails just a few inches over the leaping Prior and runs away for a boundary
and Johnson launches a powerful drive back past the bowler and gets another valuable boundary
oh dear, Shahzad is absolutely hobbling in here, and it's a horrible result for England as he sprays a wide and therefore has to bowl again
Johnson backs away and gets a big inside edge that runs away to fine leg for three runs
Johnson backs away again and just gets a bit of bat through to Prior along the ground, Prior's underarm hits the stumps but Johnson wasn't trying for a run
Anderson strikes! Good bowling as he aims at the stumps - leg stump to be specific - and Johnson goes for the big hoick through the leg side and he's bowled
good bounce from Anderson, and Hastings defends a ball at chest height
another good bouncer! Hastings looks to guide it to third man and then pulls out, well directed by Anderson
Hastings gets off the mark with a clip through midwicket
Smith pushes hard to point and can only get a single
super shot! What a cracking drive through cover as he backs off a touch and thumps a pretty good ball that was full and straight, finding the gap at extra cover
Finn goes the slower bouncer now and Smith swipes, but can't connect
another slower ball and Smith advances, then nudges a single to cover
oh, well done by Hastings as he backs away and is followed by Finn, but Hastings then swivels a pull and helps it fine enough to beat fine leg - more valuable runs
another boundary as Hastings swings and throws everything at this one, getting it high over mid-off and gets enough on it to bounce over the boundary
another slower ball and Hastings pulls hard through midwicket to the man in the deep
Anderson uses the slower ball now and Hastings swings hard, crashing a single down to long-on
punched away through the off side
slower full toss now and Hastings can't get it away
good yorker length ball and all Hastings can do is chip a single to long-on
that's an interesting one from Smith! He's tried the reverse hook to Anderson! Didn't get anything on it, but Prior has fumbled and they pick up a bye
Hastings swings hard and gets it out through midwicket
Woakes gets five wickets! Hastings has lifted a slower ball over midwicket but straight to Collingwood in the deep, where he takes a pretty simple catch
another slower delivery and Smith throws the kitchen sink at this, slapping a single down to long-off
Woakes has six! And the 50th over may not be required after all. Lee has cut hard but in the air and third man takes the catch, it's the substitute fielder Luke Wright down there
oh, well played Steven Smith! Another slower ball from Woakes, and Smith has waited on it, driving inside out over cover and clearing the boundary, great stroke
driven away to point
bouncer from Woakes, and Dougie ducks under it
good yorker gives Woakes a chance, but Bollinger keeps it out and picks up a single
Bollinger begins with a boundary! He's cut hard and thereare men up in the circle at backward point and fly slip - this pierces the gap
crunched out to deep cover for one run, to give Smith the strike

Smith swings hard, pulls it to deep midwicket and they come back for two runs, Dougie's dive at the non-striker's end is in vain - he's short as Trott takes the throw and breaks the stumps. Australia are all out for 249.

inn2.comm: pacy start, but wildly inaccurate from Lee. Hurled well wide of off stump, and one of those slips was almost in action to stop that - before Haddin moved across
that's better! Strauss whips his bat inside the line as Lee hits a good length on off stump. A leave, rather than a miss, but the line was great
and again. Back of a length, hitting the seam and going away from the bat. Strauss watches it carefully and keeps the bat inside the line
this time he is beaten! Lee goes fuller outside off, Strauss steps half forward into the drive but is beaten on the outside edge. Lee wanders down to offer him a few tips on his technique
a hint of movement back into the left-hander, and good pace from the bowler too. Defended back down the track
feisty stuff! Banged in short by Lee, Strauss whips his head out of the way in a hurry. He dealt with a good bouncer pretty well
great finish to the over, curving gently in through the air but the pace is anything but gentle. Defended by Strauss
off the thigh pad and down to fine leg. That's good running, as they sprint back for the second
pace and bounce, and Prior didn't know much about that! He turns his head away and thrusts the bat out in hope ... but the bouncer ricochets off the glove and grille. That's got the crowd going
it's been a spirited start by Australia's new-ball bowlers, and this time Bollinger hits a length and the ball bursts past the outside edge

unorthodox, but effective! Back of a length and Prior initially set himself to pull over midwicket. The ball hit the seam and moved towards the slips, but he went through with the shot and ended up lifting it straight back over the bowler's head. One bounce, and over the rope
and he follows that up with some back-foot defence
slashed, and that flies over gully and down to third man for four! Prior is really flinging his bat into these shots, that was a thick edge but it raced away
back of a length, with a hint of width. Strauss steps back and cracks into the off side, but straight to the cover fielder
now the England captain is slashing up and over down to third man! Both batsmen keen to impose themselves early on, but this didn't bounce too far away from the fielder, Bollinger
this one leaps off a length and hits the splice as Prior hops back in defence
fuller this time, Prior is sat on the back foot though and drives to cover. Lee's fastest ball of the innings so far
and he follows it up with a much slower delivery! Spotted early by Prior, who drives to mid-on
tucked into the leg side, and they take the chance for a sprinted single
Prior clears the left leg and slaps down the ground ... that won't reach the boundary, however, as deep mid-off swoops to cut it off
wobbling around on a length, just outside off. Strauss punches into the covers, but hits the field

that's definitely hit the seam, jagging back in, and Strauss is caught in an awkward position as he sets himself for some sort of paddle-pull. The ball strikes him in the midriff and rolls into the off side
width outside off, Strauss chops down to third man

crack! All that effort from Bollinger as he charges to the crease, only to see the ball ping out of the middle of the bat and fly to the boundary in a moment. Authoritative pull from Prior, he's ticking nicely now
back of a length again, this time he opts to defend back down the track

at the other end, Strauss's absorbing battle with Lee continues! The batsman backed away to leg but Lee followed him with a sharp bouncer that had him ducking for safety, and a verbal barrage to boot!
tapped into the off side
again Strauss targets the off side, but he can't find the gap as short cover point fields the ball on the bounce
so instead, he tucks into the wide spaces on the leg side, picking up a single
close to the edge! That actually sounded like he may have got something on it, plenty of daylight between bat and ball however

bowled 'im! Lee has comprehensively won this battle, firing one at the top of off. Prior's feet went nowhere, the ball bursts past his attempted nurdle to gully and makes a mess of the stumps. Lee celebrates with a hop and a kick, and that's the first breakthrough for Australia!

two wickets in two balls! Both openers depart, England are in a hole now. Short, Strauss was quickly onto the pull but the ball didn't come off the middle of the bat, flying straight to Smith at square leg for an easy catch
slower ball, a cutter, and it's pulled down quite short. Pietersen defends
thick inside edge, that could so easily have gone back to hit the stumps! Luckily for Pietersen, it hits the body and bounces harmlessly towards the slips
hurled down on a length, outside off, and left alone
fuller, the batsman leans forward into a cautious drive and is off the mark with a scurried two
and another good leave to end the over

gone first ball! Lee strikes again! It wasn't the best ball, a touch short and angling down the leg side. Trott flicked off his hip but in the air, and Bollinger tumbles forward at short fine leg to take the catch. England are in disarray. Brett Lee is on a hat-trick...
no, short and ballooning over the ducking batsman. And what's more, he's over-stepped - it's a no-ball and his next delivery will be a Free Hit
short again, Bell flails and pops it straight up in the air. The crowd roar as Smith takes the catch, they perhaps don't quite realise what's going on ... Lee's got a smile on his face
a thick outside edge bounces down to third man ... and the return from the fielder is atrocious, yorking Haddin and they come back for another
tapped into the covers
full, straight and fast. Pushed just wide of mid-on and they dash through for one
languid drive from Bell, a good-looking shot but it goes straight to the fielder
on a length and defended by Pietersen ... who spots the opportunity for a quick single as mid-off is slow to amble in to field. Hands on hips from Bollinger
left alone outside off stump
Bell smelt that one, a bouncer bursting past his helmet and into Haddin's gloves. The 'keeper appeals, who knows why
pushed to cover point
short and Bell is on the pull, that hits the splice and loops up slowly ... but it's got enough on it to evade the fielder running back from square leg
going across the right-hander on the angle, going further off the seam, and Bell leaves alone
decent start, just short of a good length but aimed right at off stump. Pietersen gets across and defends to leg
slapped straight back down the ground, the ball scorches across the turf and over the boundary. Strong shot!

that'll have stung the hands of Hussey at short extra cover! Full and wide, absolutely slammed out the middle but straight at the fielder. He can see the funny side. Great effort to even stop that actually
full and straight, Pietersen pushes firmly back to the bowler, who parries to his right to give away a single
tucked off the pads into the leg side
Pietersen steps right across to the off side and clips a leg-stump delivery out into the deep ... Fine leg is up but deep square sprints across to keep them to two
squirted into the off side, Hussey is still close in in that catching position at cover, he dives to his left and gets a hand to it but can't quite stop the single
offcutter from Bollinger, slower and stopping in the wicket. Pietersen pushes into the leg side
Pietersen is counter-attacking in fine style here, lunging forward to smash this through the covers. There's no stopping that
extravagant leave to follow that up, KP struts down to tap the wicket
tapped to deep mid-off for one

flashed airily through gully! That would've resulted in a regulation catch in a Test match, but here it's a single down to third man. Keeps the bowler interested though, and that's the end of the first Powerplay
glanced behind square on the leg side

the first really testing delivery Johnson has bowled today, and it goes for four! Pietersen was caught on the crease, the ball leaving him off the pitch and taking a thick edge. That beats slip, but goes fine enough to beat third man too
defended watchfully into the off side

direct hit would've been interesting here! Pietersen dropped it into the off side and both batsmen left their creases ... but Smith swoops in a flash and fires a shy at the non-striker's end. Bell dives, and the throw goes wide. He'd have been out if that had hit
tapped to deep mid-off, and a single is taken
defended down to gully off the back foot
good start from him, this ball has just started to stick in the surface and do a little, and yet another edge flies off the bat and down to third man
coming in through the air and off the seam, Bell defends with bat and pad right together
aggression from Bell, charging down the track but his drive can't pierce the off side field
tapped down towards cover, no single to be had
now he does find space, running one down to third man for an easy single
Pietersen walks down and across his stumps, and aims a controlled paddle-pull to midwicket
just past the edge! Great line from Johnson, Pietersen had to play at that. Slip, who had been moved, is back in place
nudged into the leg side for one
chopped down to third man
a bit of bat, a bit of pad, and as the ball rolls to midwicket - with Johnson in hot pursuit - they scamper through for one

everything was right about this ball, tucking Bell up nicely in defence, except for the fact that he's been called for a no-ball. That's a bit harsh, he was certainly tight on the line but it was a borderline call. Free Hit coming up
back of a length, Bell makes room and flaps over mid-off. White sprints after it but can't pull it back in time
and defence to finish the over
Pietersen charges down the wicket but Hastings spots him coming and responds with a canny slower-ball bouncer ... that's a bit too short though, and it's called wide
pushed into the gap between mid-off and cover, quick single
Bell is dancing down the track now, but can't get to the pitch
nicely driven by Bell, stretching well forward, but there's a sweeper out on the cover boundary
full, pushed to point
great shot, intelligent batting. Back of a length and Pietersen picks up four with the latest of late cuts, a deft little shot that beats third man
straighter from Hastings, Pietersen taps to point
Bell hops down the track and sends the ball back to the bowler ... KP had backed up quite far and Johnson was on the ball in a flash, he's safely back to his crease though
tapped down, straight to the man at gully on the bounce
this time it's Smith at point doing the fielding, diving to his left to stop Bell's shot. Good effort from him
nicely straight from Johnson, Bell stays deep in the crease and defends
short and pacy from Johnson, Bell is hurried as he tries to pull ... the ball hits something though, the bat handle or the glove, and they take a single
inside edge ... the ball rolls back close to the stumps but Pietersen shows good awareness to quickly flick it away and avert the danger
Bell advances and then defends
Bell defends back down towards Hastings
short ball now and Bell turns a hook around the corner to Bollinger at fine leg
Hastings goes for the bouncer now and Pietersen ducks underneath it
quick single now as KP walks across and nudges it wide of point
driven uppishly, shouts of catch it as it sails through cover but it is safe and Bell picks up two runs to the man in the deep
some turn away from Pietersen, who punches through cover gently for a run
Bell advances and lofts this high but safely over cover and it lobs into the outfield
cut hard through cover to the man in the deep
a big stride forward from Pietersen as Smith drags the length back, the batsman defends
tossed up on middle stump, Pietersen clips to Hussey at short midwicket

tossed up and Pietersen drives back to Smith, who dives and nearly makes a catch, but there's no reaction from anyone. Hold on, though, Smith is saying he's not sure if he's taken it. He's come up with the ball clutched to his body. Asad Rauf believes it's not out but checks with the third umpire, who can easily see that ball has hit the hands, bounced while Smith is diving and then he has clutched it to his chest. Not out.
clipped away through square leg
tip and run from Pietersen as he nudges to cover
pushed back down the pitch
a good punchy drive through cover from Bell, who picks up a single to the man in the deep
Pietersen advances down the pitch again, and then clips defensively to leg
slower ball now and Pietersen drives on the bounce to Clarke at short cover
Bell advances to Smith and drives edgily and uppishly over cover point, it bounces safely short of the fielder
solidly defended back to the bowler
quicker and flatter, and it's punched through cover
well played by Bell as he takes this one off middle stump and dabs a paddle sweep fine enough to get two runs
tossed up on leg stump, it's clipped to midwicket
on the pads and it's tickled around the corner to short fine leg
cut hard forward of point and another easy single
slower short ball now and Pietersen pulls over midwicket
walks down the pitch and dabs outside off but Hastings goes wide enough to beat the bat
fullish and straight, Bell drives a bump ball down to mid-off, where the fielder dives across but can't stop it
pushed to mid-off again and this time Clarke does get across to cut it off
goes for the pull now and he can't connect
Bell dances down the pitch and drives to cover
a little shorter now and Bell cuts to deep point
Pietersen now uses his feet to Smith, but then checks his shot
and now Pietersen turns this into a full toss and swipes it across wide of midwicket
drifting in to the pads, and soft hands from KP as he nudges it to leg
good bowling, Pietersen advances and Smith sends it in flatter and quicker, the batsman has to check his shot again
lovely fielding by David Hussey at gully, as he launches himself to his right to save a good late cut from Bell that might have run away to the boundary
slower ball now, which is chipped through square leg and they can't justify a second run
driven hard through cover for another easy run

Pietersen is gone! Oh, John Hastings has done it with the slower bouncer! It has absolutely stopped in mid-air on the way to Pietersen, who wants to pull hard but is playing too quickly and ends up swinging one-handed and gets a top edge that's taken by Lee at mid-on
on the pads and Morgan can't get it away
good yorker now but Morgan manages to drive it wide of cover to get off the mark
tossed up well outside off and Morgan steps across to work it through the leg side
good flight from Smith, and Bell uses the feet and then drives to mid-on
cut away to point and can't find the gap
driven to long-off for a comfortable single

another one goes! Morgan has holed out to Smith! Not a very clever piece of batting, you'd have to say, as he gets underneath a lofted drive and skies it to long-off, where Johnson runs around to his right and takes a catch that nearly bobbles out of his hands.
Bell reaches at this one and pushes to point
Collingwood is beaten outside off first ball, there's no foot movement there as he just tries to dab a cut away
this time Collingwood gets across to defend with a straight bat
soft hands from Collingwood as he nudges to leg and gets off the mark
walks across this time and clips it to leg
bouncer from Hastings and Bell pulls, just getting over the top of it to get a run to square leg
another bouncer wide of off, Collingwood barely even moves as he leaves this one alone
Smith tosses this one up on off stump and Bell drives down to long-off
Collingwood leans forward and defends
fuller ball and Collingwood clips to mid-on
on the back foot now, Collingwood crunches a cut through cover point
a bit of a long hop here but it's not put away as Bell pulls a single down towards long-on
Collingwood defends solidly
Bell tries to dab a cut away fine but this one beats the bat
driven hard but straight to mid-off
slower ball - and much slower at 104kph - and it's driven to mid-on

gone! Bell has played on and Hastings has got rid of both the well-set batsmen in KP and Bell. This one swings in and Bell tries for the late cut, the movement does him in and his bottom edge runs on to the off stump
Woakes gets off the mark straight away with a thickish edge to third man
fullish and angling in to Collingwood, who gets a single as his drive is knocked down at short cover
a tad short from Smith and Woakes punches it wide of mid-off
tries for the pull but can't get it away
well flighted and Woakes drives to cover
another one is driven through the off side, this time through the gap at cover
really tossed up to tempt the batsman, Smith dives across to save the off-drive off his own bowling
punched through extra cover for a single
Hastings angles this in and attacks the stumps, it's driven to mid-on
driven towards mid-off this time and can't find the gap
a good shot now from Collingwood, he's just forced this flick wide of mid-on, just placed well enough to find the gap and it runs away for a boundary
soft hands now as Collingwood clips through midwicket and races back for two runs
bouncer, and this one looked too high but the umpires have been very lenient today on such decisions and again a wide is not called
but this one is called a wide as Collingwood walks across outside off and Hastings sends it much wider
beaten outside off, just a good length delivery that angles in and Collingwood played the wrong line
pushed back to the bowler who does his own fielding
cut to backward point where White does the fielding
slower and shorter, Woakes waits on it and turns a single through square leg
driven down towards long-on, just another gentle single
pushed down to long-off now and another single
oooh, a touch edgy here as Collingwood leans forward and gets it off the shoulder of the bat, the ball lobs up but well short of Smith
banged in on the hips and it's clipped uppishly to square leg
again it's soft hands from Collingwood, who nudges a single to midwicket
angled across Woakes, who cuts to backward point
bouncer now from Johnson, and it's ducked by Woakes
driven away through cover for another single
clipped away through square leg
flicked through leg for some more runs
driven back past the bowler
pushed down to long-off, where Bollinger does the fielding
punched wide of cover this time
well flighted by Smith and Woakes goes for the dab sweep around the corner
pushed straight to Clarke at cover
pushed right across Woakes, who tries for the square drive but can't connect
beaten outside off this time
opens the face and tries to run a single through point but just finds the fielder
again the angle across Woakes is difficult for the batsman, who tries to drive and is beaten
pushed to point and can't find a run
and that's a maiden, as Woakes defends the last ball

and Watson strikes with his first ball! Collingwood decided he was going after the medium-pacer and lofted it high over mid-on, Hastings began in the circle and ran halfway back to the boundary to take an outstanding catch running with the flight of the ball.
pushed away defensively to the off side
tickled down leg side and is that a dropped chance? Haddin diving to his left has missed the take with his left hand, but it's hard to see what that has come off - perhaps off the trousers. Not bat.
pushed away defensively
tries to force this through leg but can't connect
bouncer and it's caught behind! Watson has two in his first over! Woakes has tried to hook this one and got a tickle through to Haddin
sharp bouncer greets Shahzad! He wears it on the chest, and there are plenty of words being flung around too
not the greatest follow-up, much too wide outside off stump
Johnson re-adjusts his line, a nervous waft from the batsman
Shahzad is forward and driving without any great conviction, and he's easily beaten on the outside edge
Johnson is firing it past the edge at will when he gets it right, as he does now. Shahzad's feet go nowhere as he stands at the crease to defend
the bowler attacks the stumps, this time the bat comes down in time to keep the ball out
pushed full again but slightly wider of off, yet again the ball flies past the edge of the bat
short on off stump, Anderson sways out of the way
another bouncer from Watson, this is much too short and balloons over the batsman
back of a length, outside off and oast the edge
another nervous swish from Anderson, not sure how much longer England's tail can survive these conditions
edged! Off the shoulder of the bat though, and the ball loops over a leaping second slip
booming cover drive this time ... but he hits nothing but fresh air

short on off stump to end the over, Anderson tries to uppercut it but again can't get a touch on it. Watto wanders down and stares in disbelief. Could easily have a had a third wicket any number of times in this over
on a length, but outside off and Shahzad leaves alone
dug in shorter and much faster by Johnson, the ball rises on Shahzad but he rides the bounce and plays it down to gully
bouncer from Johnson! He's got Shahzad hopping nervously, and the umpire calls one for the over with a wide smile on his face
this one hits the seam and jags away, past the edge for the umpteenth time

aimed at the top of middle, nudged to short third man and there's utter confusion between the three Englishmen out there - Shahzad has a runner remember - which really should've resulted in a run-out. The throw is wide, however
just short of a length, tapped down to point
appeal as a good bouncer hits something on the way throught to Haddin ... was that off the shoulder? Not off the bat, reckons Umpire Rauf, and calls one for the over
nudged off the hip, and an easy single into the leg side
and Anderson rotates the strike straight away with another quick single
great line and length from Watson, again he's past the edge, but he's over-stepped so the next ball is going to be a Free Hit
Shahzad takes full toll, swinging mightily to send a length ball sailing over wide long-on! 84 metre boundary there
and he follows that up with studied defence
full on middle and leg, flicked to midwicket
Shahzad continues to cling limpet-like to the crease, defending this
banged into the pitch, the ball rises past the edge of the bat
tapped down defensively to gully, nothing in the batsman's half
there's spite and malice in this bouncer! Shahzad was in no position to play it, throwing the hands out. The ball takes the splice of the bat and lobs up, falling just past the stumps
yet again past the edge. Surely, eventually, he'll get a touch on one of these?
there we go! Very full outside off, Shahzad flings his bat into a drive and a thick edge ends up nestled in a tumbling Brad Haddin's gloves. Australia just one wicket away now
short on off stump, Anderson gives himself room and flashes wildly, play-and-a-miss
on a length, guided down to that man at deep gully/short third man
dug in short, past Anderson's grille as he plays a classic tailender's waft
fuller, wider, and driven off the toe of the bat to cover
that one's come out of the middle! Smeared over mid-on by Anderson, one bounce and over the rope
well, he was aiming to send this one into the stratosphere, just shutting his eyes and heaving wildly to leg. Nowhere near it
full on off stump, Finn taps to mid-on
England's No. 11 is ducking now as Bollinger sends down a bouncer. One for the over, says the umpire
not the worst shot by Finn, backing away and cracking a length delivery up and over cover. Not enough on it to reach the boundary, however
slap! Anderson is starting to middle a couple now. He comes charging down the wicket and smashes this through extra cover
slower ball from Bollinger, not picked at all by Anderson who is through with the shot before the ball gets to him, but they pick up one into the leg side all the same
England's tailenders are enjoying themselves now! Just short of a good length, Finn just opens his stance and swings this straight down the ground, standing to admire the shot as the ball sails away
Anderson immediately backs away and tries to cut, past the edge
tapped down just to gully's right, they hurry through for one

short, and Finn is left lying on the ground in ungainly fashion as he gets out of the way of that. Slower-ball bouncer. Finn obviously likes the feel of the wicket against his derriere, he falls over enough when he's bowling
short again, dealt with much more effectively this time
fired full and straight, but Finn's bat comes down in good time
on a length around off stump, Finn gives himself some room and cracks it towards mid-off. Clarke does well to cut the shot off
just short of a good length, Finn positions himself for an ambitious pull but the ball flies between bat and body and through to the keeper
full and straight, swiped across the line into the leg side
Bollinger aims for the yorker, gets it slightly wrong and Anderson gets bat on the full toss to pick up another single
heaved into the leg side, that's found the gap and Finn collects another boundary!
now he's charging down the track and slogging wildly, Bollinger pushes it slightly wider of off and Finn gets nowhere near it
straight back over the bowler's head, baseball style! Well, England may not have any chance of winning this, but the batsman are having fun. Making a bit of dosh for charity too, which is good
slashed down to third man for one
big swing, big miss
Finn is knocked off his feet by a searing yorker! Somehow he's found a way to keep that out...
full and fast again, Finn makes room and taps gently to cover
slower-ball bouncer from Lee, an almighty heave from Finn but he doesn't get near it
another slower ball, this time he spots it and clobbers it over midwicket!
ooh, that's nasty. That's slipped out as a very high full toss - a beamer really - at about sternum height. The ball evades Haddin too
that's more like it. On a length and aimed at the stumps, tapped to gully

Anderson gives himself acres of room as Bollinger fires in a yorker outside off, in fact Anderson has given himself so much room that he almost tumbles over towards square leg. Nowhere near hitting it
tapped straight to Hussey at cover, they set off for a suicidal single and the throw is wide
another boundary for Finn! He picks up the length early and swings this away to wide midwicket
much fuller, slapped to long-on for one
Anderson backs away, trying to open up the off side, but completely misses a length delivery from Bollinger

well Finn has got an excellent connection on this one too! Full and straight from Lee, the batsman cracks it in the air to wide long-on and only a great piece of fielding from Hastings saves the boundary
yorker, outside off, and it slips right under Anderson's bat
back of a length, Anderson tries to run it down to third man but ball beats bat
Anderson backs right away to leg and slashes a square drive out into the deep. They run hard and are easily back for the second when the throw arrives at the stumps
full and straight, Anderson defends awkwardly to cover
on a length, angling across the left-hander and he pulls his bat inside the line to leave
into the stands! What a shot from Finn, gunbarrel straight, a monstrous hit and there's the fifty partnership. Highest 10th wicket partnership by England in an ODI
just past the off stump! Finn looked like a batsman hitting that six, now he's a tailender as he closes his eyes and swings wildly to leg
there it is, finally. Another ugly heave from Finn, the ball flicks the bail and that's a series win for Australia. Although not without a few flutters during this partnership, you'd think
